  "text": "The trough level in this case was below 2 ng/mL, lower than the recommended therapeutic dose for human IBD. However, effectiveness was observed. All cytokine production was inhibited completely at a blood level of 1 ng/mL in a basic study of tacrolimus in humans; the 50% inhibitory concentration was 0.02 -0.11 ng/mL and an inhibitory effect was indicated by a low concentration [CITATION_1] . The trough level was not recorded in a report on tacrolimus for the treatment of sterile panniculitis in a dog, but the effect was observed at a low dose of 0.06 mg/kg/day [17] . Therefore, there is a possibility that even a low dose and a low trough level can be effective in dogs. However, because in this case, tacrolimus was given every other day, the resulting lower total protein and albumin levels indicated the need for daily administration.",
